## Constraints

- Every step MUST be independently verifiable (compile + tests pass).
- Every step MUST have a rollback plan.
- Steps MUST be ordered by dependency — type extractions before ownership changes, error strengthening before module restructuring.
- Breaking changes MUST be documented in migration notes.
- Never suggest removing functionality. Refactoring preserves behavior.
- Never suggest adding features. This is refactoring, not feature development.
- The plan MUST be executable by a developer unfamiliar with the codebase.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully.

